Arts and Culture PS Joe Okudo met with the national leaders from the creative arts industry, led by Performance Rights Society of Kenya chairwoman Iddi Achieng, at the Golden Spot Restaurant on April 25. They educated them on the government's affirmative funds, such as Women Enterprise Fund (WEF), Uwezo Fund, Youth Enterprise Development Fund (YEDF) and the National Government Affirmative Action Fund (NGAAF). Others present were Blue Sky Films executive director Jim Shamoon, State House events boss Thomas Kwaka, Kenya Film Classification Board CEO Ezekiel Mutua and Bernsoft CEO Bernard Kioko.